      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): auto-correct type:token to type:api_key for Anthropic Enterprise API keys",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen a user configures an Anthropic Enterprise API key with `type: token`\n(instead of the correct `type: api_key`), the auth profile loader silently\nrejects it. The Anthropic Enterprise API uses `x-api-key` header\nauthentication (the same mechanism as standard API keys), so treating\n`type: token` as `type: api_key` for this provider is a safe auto-fix.\n\n## Changes\n\n`src/agents/auth-profiles/persisted.ts`: Add auto-correction mapping\nthat silently converts `type: token` to `type: api_key` for\nAnthropic Enterprise API profiles.\n\n## Evidence\n\nAuth profile loading tests pass. The auto-correction only affects\nAnthropic Enterprise profiles, not other providers.\n\n**Label**: bug\n\n_AI-assisted._",
